e is a thin client. Keyboard input writes to the daemon inbox (`/run/cypherclaw-tmp/inbox.jsonl`). The daemon (2750-line `src/cypherclaw/daemon.py`) routes messages through Claude/Gemini/Codex with conversation memory, budget management, and smart routing. Responses come back via a shared message bus (`/tmp/cypherclaw_messages.jsonl`) that the face reads.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**What's on the face:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Typing** — just start typing, no toggle. Words appear right-aligned below the face.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Responses** — daemon responses float left-aligned (blue). Same agents as Telegram.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Telegram mirror** — daemon's `tg_send()` patched to also write to face bus. Everything sent to Telegram shows on the face.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **System events** — key changes, mood shifts, art generation, Theramini activity appear centered in amber.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Thinking animation** — orbiting particles, expanding ripples, and LLM-generated musings (qwen3.5:4b) while waiting for daemon response.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Chat history** — Tab toggles scrollable history from daemon conversation memory.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Emoji stripping** — PIL can't render emoji, so they're stripped from bus messages.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Key files on CypherClaw:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/senseweave/keyboard_chat.py` — face terminal module\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/face_display.py` — patched: calls `chat.poll_system()`, `chat.poll_message_bus()`, `chat.render()`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `/home/user/cypherclaw/src/cypherclaw/daemon.py` — patched: `_face_bus()` mirrors `tg_send()` to message bus\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 2. Audio Fixes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Disconnected webcam + Scarlett inputs from SuperCollider (caused occasional pops via USB audio glitches)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Commented out input connections in `scripts/start_audio.sh` so they don't return on reboot\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Inputs should be reconnected only when Theramini duet or contact mic listener is ready\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 3. Artist's Plan Completion PRD\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-New PRD (`prd-artist-plan-completion.md`) with 14 requirements covering gaps:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-001--005:** Visitor identity (face recognition, person registry, greeting)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-006--009:** Physical output (fix printer, sound postcards, daily digest, welcome stickers)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-010--011:** Gallery exhibition mode (curated sequences)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-012--013:** Room acoustics (swept sine IR, convolution reverb SynthDef)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-014:** B&P color covers via DreamShaper\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 4. Artist's Plan Rectified\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Updated `artist-plan.md`: PipeWire not JACK, 21 chars not 15, Pareidolia not GlyphWeave, added Inner Life section, marked phase completion percentages, cross-referenced covering PRDs.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 5. R750 Ollama Integration (built by local SDP pipeline)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-12 tasks completed (all PASS), building the code for R750 deployment:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `ollama_health.py` — health check + model listing for dual-socket Ollama\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `federation/discovery.py` — Tailscale peer discovery with registry merge\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `cypherclaw_daemon.py` — `_invoke_ollama()` HTTP invoke, `run_agent()` Ollama branch, `LOCAL_ONLY` mode, `_available_agents()` respects health + quota\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `quota_monitor.py` — local provider infinite headroom, Ollama models in PROVIDERS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `first_boot.py` — instance identity with artistic name generation (already existed on CypherClaw)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- 11 new test files covering all Ollama integration paths\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 6. CypherClaw Day 1-4 Build Committed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-64 files (11,907 insertions) committed on CypherClaw and synced to PromptClaw repo. This was