ystemd unit or cron is respawning it. The daemon handles Telegram — telegram_commands should stay disabled.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-3. **Face display sometimes has two processes** — kill both and restart one cleanly\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-4. **APC-010/011 need_split** — gallery exhibition tasks flagged as too broad, the pipeline will auto-split them\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### R750 Deployment\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The integration code is built and tested. When deploying:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-1. Complete bare metal runbook (`docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md`)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-2. Run model evaluation plan (`docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md`)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-3. Update model names in `OLLAMA_MODELS` routing config (currently placeholders)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-4. SCP the modified files to R750\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-5. Set `LOCAL_ONLY=true` in `.env` for full local inference mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Keyboard Chat on CypherClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The face terminal is working but could use:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Better font rendering (consider rendering text to a separate surface for anti-aliasing)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The `expression_override` property exists on `KeyboardChat` — wire it into `face_display.py` so the face goes \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"curious\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" while thinking\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Long daemon responses get cut off — consider word-wrapping at render time (already implemented but test with real long responses)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Key Architectural Decisions Made This Session\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-1. **Face is a thin client** — no LLM calls, no Telegram polling. All intelligence goes through the daemon. The daemon is the single source of truth for conversation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-2. **Message bus pattern** — JSONL append files for inter-process communication. Simple, atomic, no dependencies.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-3. **Thinking animation uses local LLM** — qwen3.5:4b generates contextual musings while the real agents work. Nice UX, trivial cost.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-4. **Two pipelines in parallel** — CypherClaw runs the main task queue, MacBook runs R750 prep. Different PRDs, different queues, same codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Git State\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **PromptClaw** (MacBook): `feat/graceful-degradation` branch, pushed to GitHub\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **CypherClaw**: `agent/t1/demo-day-caveats` branch, pushed to cypherclaw-private\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- These are different repos (`exquest/PromptClaw` vs `exquest/cypherclaw-private`) with overlapping content under different directory structures (`my-claw/tools/` vs `tools/`)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Progress\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Generated from SQLite state (`tasks`, `task_runs`, `escalations`). Do not edit manually.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ETC: ~3h 45m remaining (24 tasks, low confidence, calibrating)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Expected completion: 1:39 AM tomorrow.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Progress: [███████████████░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░] 38%  15 / 39 tasks complete\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  completed: 15, pending: 24, blocked: 0, skipped: 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-001@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-002@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-003@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-004@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-005@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-006@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-007@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-008@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-009@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-010@20260408T223256Z**: split —