CHANGELOG.md:633:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifacts read path (frac-0040): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes `ArtifactManager.read_events()` which parses `events.jsonl` line by line and reconstructs the same `Event` dataclass shape that `append_event()` writes, returning `[]` when the log file does not yet exist. The four filename-taking write helpers (`write_prompt`, `write_output`, `write_handoff`, `write_summary`) now reject empty/whitespace-only filenames with `ValueError` before any I/O, matching the orchestrator's existing call-site contract while failing fast at the boundary. Existing public method signatures, on-disk filenames, JSONL serialization shape, and orchestrator call sites are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_depth.py` pins the round-trip read, missing-log empty result, empty-filename rejection across the four filename helpers, normal-filename acceptance, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` and `tests/test_config.py` remain the regression anchors for end-to-end run behavior and config loading.
CHANGELOG.md:635:- Added depth-2 PromptClaw model diagnostics (frac-0039): `promptclaw/models.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigModelReport` plus typed helpers `sorted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, `config_model_report`, `summarize_config_model`, `summarize_route_decision`, and `summarize_run_state` so config, route, agent, and run dataclasses can emit deterministic JSON-safe operator summaries without changing existing dataclass fields or orchestration call sites. The narrative ASGI entry point `cypherclaw.narrative_api.main:app` now calls `bootstrap_identity()` before app creation, matching the `python -m cypherclaw.narrative_api` startup path so first boots mint and persist identity automatically. `tests/test_promptclaw_models_depth.py` pins model summary counts, sorted JSON-safe output, route/run summaries, an end-to-end orchestrator run summary, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_narrative_api_main.py` now pins ASGI import identity persistence between boots, while existing config/router/orchestrator and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:697:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:707:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:731:- Added a steady-state SDP cap summary (T-032@c): `promptclaw.sdp_cost` now exposes `DailyCapCheck`, `CostCapSummary`, `read_csv`, `check_daily_caps`, `summarize_daily_cap`, `render_cap_summary`, and `write_cap_summary`, plus optional CLI flags `--summary-out`, `--daily-cap-usd`, and `--min-days`. The committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cap-summary.md` links to `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md`, checks seven active UTC days from `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` against the documented `$5.00` daily cap, and reports **FAIL** with seven breaches. Regression coverage in `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` pins exact-at-cap pass behavior, breach overage formatting, minimum-day failure behavior, CLI failure status on breach, and the committed summary artifact.
CHANGELOG.md:733:- Added a steady-state SDP cost extractor and committed CSV (T-032@b): `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` exposes `TOKEN_PRICING`, `match_pricing`, `call_cost_usd`, `DailyCostRow`, `extract_steady_state_cost`, and `write_csv`, applying the substring-matched pricing table from `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` (claude-opus-4 $15/$75, claude-sonnet-4 $3/$15, claude-haiku $0.80/$4, gpt-4o $2.50/$10, o3 $10/$40, codex-mini $1.50/$6, fallback $3/$15) to per-task `lead_profile_id` rows in the `.sdp/state.db` `telemetry` table. The CLI `python -m promptclaw.sdp_cost --db .sdp/state.db --days 7 --out sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` rolls the 7 most recent active UTC days into the committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` (header `date,runs,input_tokens,output_tokens,cache_creation_tokens,cache_read_tokens,total_cost_usd,models`); `cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, and `thinking_tokens` are reported but not billed, matching the cost-model.md formula. Test coverage in `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` pins the pricing table values, substring-and-fallback matching, the cost-model.md worked example (`(in/1e6*in_p)+(out/1e6*out_p)`), per-day grouping with sorted unique tier lists, the locked CSV header schema with 4-decimal USD formatting and `|`-joined models, and the CLI's stdout path echo.
CHANGELOG.md:761:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:795:- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
CHANGELOG.md:807:- Made the self-monitor more truthful: `self_listener.py` now derives glyph-facing brightness and motion from captured audio features instead of target-only metadata, while `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` pins the live meter to the verified JACK path on CypherClaw and still leaves PipeWire / `pw-jack` capture as fallback code paths.
CHANGELOG.md:808:- Fixed the remaining live self-monitor blackout path: when direct `jack_rec` capture times out, `self_listener.py` now falls back to analyzing a fresh `/tmp/room_capture.wav` clip instead of writing a dark `capture_timeout` state, so glyph and sampler decisions stay audio-derived on boxes where the JACK recorder hangs.
CHANGELOG.md:813:- Hardened the live audio runtime after the Scarlett/JACK outage: `start_audio.sh` now links the repo SynthDef bundle into `~/.local/share/SuperCollider/synthdefs`, starts `scsynth` with synthdef auto-load enabled, and prefers a real JACK/Scarlett graph before falling back to `pw-jack`; `restart_composer.sh` now restarts the composer gracefully and verifies the new PID instead of rebuilding synthdefs with `/d_recv`; and `cypherclaw_boot.sh` no longer blindly sends `/n_set` to master node `99999` after boot.
CHANGELOG.md:814:- Tightened that audio-runtime recovery again so `start_audio.sh` only stays on the real-JACK path when `system:playback_1` is actually present, and it now retries `scsynth` on `pw-jack` automatically if the real JACK graph disappears or never registers `SuperCollider:out_1`.
CHANGELOG.md:815:- Made the Scarlett recovery path deterministic: when real JACK needs to be rebuilt, `start_audio.sh` now clears stale JACK state, relaunches `jackdbus`, and configures the ALSA backend for `hw:USB` before starting `scsynth`, so the box can recover onto the Scarlett monitor path instead of drifting into a PipeWire-only fallback.
CHANGELOG.md:821:- Made `self_listener.py` backend-aware: it now auto-selects between `jack_rec` and `pw-jack jack_rec`, sets `JACK_NO_START_SERVER=1` on its capture probes to avoid waking an unwanted JACK server, and publishes `capture_backend` in `/tmp/self_listen.json` so operators can tell which live graph the meter is following.
CHANGELOG.md:823:- Made the cold-boot meter less ambiguous: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now chooses `SELF_LISTENER_CAPTURE_BACKEND` from the boot-time graph decision, preferring a live PipeWire sink monitor before JACK fallbacks, and it performs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start room/sampler/face daemons from other boot hooks are collapsed back to one process each.
CHANGELOG.md:824:- Swapped the self-listener toward a host-stable monitor path: `self_listener.py` now prefers a PipeWire sink monitor target when one is available, still falls back to direct JACK or `pw-jack` port capture when needed, and keeps the old backend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.
CHANGELOG.md:835:- Promoted the Perform-VE room mic to the actual live capture path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `room_listener.py` without `--no-jack`, and `room_listener.py` now reports `capture_backend` / `capture_source` so the live state shows whether JACK on the condenser path or an ALSA fallback is in use.
CHANGELOG.md:836:- Adjusted room-listener fallback priority so ALSA auto-selection now prefers the Perform-VE interface over webcam or generic analog capture when JACK is unavailable.
CHANGELOG.md:838:- Made Perform-VE usable through the Linux audio stack by teaching `room_listener.py` to prefer a PipeWire `pw-record` target for Perform-VE before trying JACK or ALSA fallbacks.
CHANGELOG.md:956:- Added artifact-based handoff flow for lead, verify, and clarification phases.
