sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:9:**Public-facing target:** `cypherclaw.holdenu.com` (Cloudflare-fronted, R2 storage, Worker for routing/HLS)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:16:CypherClaw is an autonomous music-making entity that has been running continuously for ~12 days at the time of this PRD, composing through a SuperCollider-driven duet composer with seven voices (pluck, breath, choir, kotekan, pad, bowed, tabla_tin) across scenes whose arc phases cycle Listen / Conversation / Divination / Procession. It currently outputs through one master reverb on a JACK graph and is heard only inside the room where the box lives.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:39:- Real `jackd` on `hw:USB` Scarlett (PID 1337) — not the PipeWire-JACK shim
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:65:- JACK only. `jack_rec` exists for recording to disk.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:79:- Cloudflare Worker (TypeScript) at `worker/` with `wrangler.toml`, handles `/api/*` for `explorer.holdenu.com`
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:80:- R2 bucket for audio storage with byte-range proxy via `GET /api/stream/:trackId`
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:82:- No `cypherclaw.holdenu.com` subdomain exists yet — Cloudflare DNS + Worker route needed
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:115:- **Approve cost-bearing changes** — anything that would incur new Cloudflare Worker billing (currently free tier), R2 storage spend, or external compute. PRD anticipates staying within free tiers; if a feature requires paid services, escalate.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:116:- **Approve credential changes** — Cloudflare API tokens for `cypherclaw.holdenu.com` DNS, R2 access for upload.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:183:- **Encoding (on cypherclaw):** `audio_streamer.py` daemon subscribes to JACK output bus, runs Opus encoding via `pyogg` or shells `opusenc`/`ffmpeg`. Produces 6-second Opus segments at ~96 kbps. Each segment HTTP-POSTed to the Cloudflare Worker.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:184:- **Segment/playlist management (Cloudflare Worker, extends existing holdenu-api worker):**
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:185:  - `POST /api/cypherclaw/segment` — receives a binary segment + metadata header (sequence number, duration, current scene, current tuning). Stores in R2 under `cypherclaw/live/{YYYY-MM-DD}/seg-{seq}.opus`. Updates `live.m3u8` HLS playlist (last ~10 segments).
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:186:  - `GET /api/cypherclaw/live.m3u8` — serves current playlist (no auth).
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:187:  - `GET /api/cypherclaw/segment/{path}` — serves segment from R2 with byte-range support.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:188:  - `GET /api/cypherclaw/live-features` — Server-Sent Events stream of live audio features + scene metadata + current tuning. cypherclaw POSTs periodically to a feature-update endpoint; Worker fans out via Durable Object.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:191:- **Session archival:** When the composer transitions out of a long "session" (definition TBD by engineering; suggest: a continuous span >= 8 minutes with reasonable rms variance), `session_archiver.py` selects representative segments, concatenates into a single Opus file, computes the title per CypherClaw's pattern (`{House-Imagery} / {Tuning-Character} — {DD Month}`), uploads to R2 under `cypherclaw/archive/{session_id}/`, and records metadata.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:192:- **Page (`cypherclaw.holdenu.com`):** Static page served by Cloudflare Worker or Pages. HTML structure:
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:193:  - `<audio>` element pointing at `live.m3u8` (hls.js polyfill for non-Safari browsers)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:197:- **DNS / TLS:** New Cloudflare DNS A/AAAA records for `cypherclaw.holdenu.com` → Worker route. Reuse existing Cloudflare zone.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:201:- `my-claw/tools/audio_streamer.py` (Opus encoder + HTTP poster)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:203:- `catalog-explorer/worker/src/cypherclaw.ts` (new Worker module for cypherclaw routes)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:210:- `catalog-explorer/worker/wrangler.toml` (R2 bindings, route for cypherclaw.holdenu.com)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:378:| CC-020 | `audio_streamer.py` produces Opus segments at approximately 6 seconds and approximately 96 kbps from the JACK output bus. | MUST | T2 | Segment files on disk show the expected duration and bitrate; the streamer process consumes under 10% CPU. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:379:| CC-021 | Cloudflare Worker accepts segment POSTs at `/api/cypherclaw/segment` and stores them in R2. | MUST | T2 | Test POST writes a segment to R2 and the object is retrievable via R2 listing. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:380:| CC-022 | Cloudflare Worker serves a valid HLS playlist at `/api/cypherclaw/live.m3u8`. | MUST | T1 | `hls.js` validator (or `ffplay`) successfully plays the live stream. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:381:| CC-023 | The `cypherclaw.holdenu.com` DNS record plus Worker route resolves over HTTPS with a valid certificate. | MUST | T1 | `curl -I https://cypherclaw.holdenu.com/` returns 200 with `cf-ray` header. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:383:| CC-025 | `session_archiver.py` produces a session approximately every 8 minutes or more, names it per CypherClaw's pattern (`{House-Imagery} / {Tuning-Character} — {DD Month}`), and uploads it to the R2 archive path. | MUST | T2 | After 30 minutes of synthetic uptime, at least 3 sessions appear in R2 with the expected naming and metadata. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:386:| CC-028 | End-to-end test confirms a tone-generator signal flows from JACK through the streamer, Worker, R2, and back to a browser `<audio>` element within 30 seconds. | MUST | T2 | End-to-end test passes in CI or scripted run; latency measurement is logged. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:387:| CC-090 | The composer publishes live MIDI events (note_on, note_off, control_change, pitch_bend) to a `live_midi_emitter.py` daemon that batches and POSTs them to the Cloudflare Worker's `/api/cypherclaw/midi-event` endpoint. Events are tagged with voice, scene, and tuning context. | MUST | T2 | Integration test: a scripted composer arc emits notes; the Worker receives the batched MIDI events with the expected metadata within 500 ms of emission. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:388:| CC-091 | The Cloudflare Worker exposes a `/api/cypherclaw/live-midi` WebSocket (Durable Object backed) that fans out received MIDI events to connected browser clients with sub-second latency. | MUST | T2 | Integration test: a browser client subscribes to the WebSocket; events POSTed to `/api/cypherclaw/midi-event` arrive at the client within 1 second. |
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:486:- T-002: Add Worker route for `cypherclaw.holdenu.com` in wrangler.toml + worker/src/index.ts
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:488:- T-004: Implement HLS playlist endpoint (GET /api/cypherclaw/live.m3u8)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:492:- T-008: Implement `audio_streamer.py` Opus encoder + JACK reader + segment poster on cypherclaw
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:493:- T-009: Deploy audio_streamer as systemd unit on cypherclaw
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:499:- T-015: End-to-end smoke test (tone → JACK → R2 → page → playback)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:628:- Tone generator → JACK → audio_streamer → Worker → R2 → page audio element → playback (latency < 30s)
