# catalog-explorer — Claude Code Project Context

## Project Identity

```yaml
name: catalog-explorer
one_liner: 3D mind-map for the 402-track Be Holden U catalog. Static HTML + 3d-force-graph; runs from file://, no server required. Anthony explores his own catalog with mouse + keyboard, finds buried gems, and (Phase 2) edits mood / status / story / manual links in-place.
audience: Anthony Holden Ainsworth (private working tool)
status: active
business_role: supporting
revenue_stage: n/a
tags: [ct_business, music, ai_infra]
related_projects: [holdenu, ProjectDocumentation, LifeImprover]
license: Proprietary
```

## Notes for agents

- **Static-only by design (v1).** No build step. No HTTP server. `file://`
  works because `data/catalog.js` is a `.js` file that sets a global, not
  a `.json` file fetched at runtime.
- **Source CSV is owned elsewhere.** The CSV at
  `~/Documents/programming/LifeImprover/communications_channel/2026-04-27-be-holden-u-catalog.csv`
  is the upstream data. Don't hand-edit `data/catalog.js` — re-run
  `build_catalog_data.py` after the CSV updates.
- **Phase 2 / Phase 3 follow-ups** are documented in `README.md`. v1 is
  intentionally read-only.

## See also

- `README.md` — usage, controls, visual encoding
- The Be Holden U release plan in
  `~/Documents/programming/LifeImprover/communications_channel/2026-04-27-music-release-plan.md`
- The catalog inventory (this tool's data source) in
  `~/Documents/programming/LifeImprover/communications_channel/2026-04-27-be-holden-u-catalog.csv`

