CHANGELOG.md:519:- Added depth-2 primary render-path end-to-end test coverage (frac-0102b): `tests/test_render_pass.py` now includes `RenderPassEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/pass_.py` public surface through one register → enable → quantity → gate → apply lifecycle: a three-rule stack registered out of canonical order (`R3`, `R1`, `R2`) with `R1` quantity-disabled, `R2` carrying `quantities={"R2": 0.5}`, and `R3` role-gated by `frozenset({"melody", "bass"})` canonicalizes to `("R1", "R2", "R3")` with `effective_k` returning `0.0`/`0.5`/`1.0`; the first `apply(...)` returns a `PerformedPart` whose `applied_rules` skip the disabled `R1`, whose `quantities` record all three effective `k` values, and whose score-tree trace carries structurally correct `rule_id`/`k`/`roles` entries for `R2` (no role gate) and `R3` (forwarded role-gate frozenset); the second `apply(...)` with `quantity_overrides={"R1": 0.75}` re-enables `R1` so `applied_rules == ("R1", "R2", "R3")` in canonical order with the override `k=0.75` reflected in both `quantities` and the trace; and a combined diagnostic of rule order, effective-k map, and both performed-part snapshots (with `frozenset` role gates explicitly converted to sorted lists) round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_render_pass_depth.py` pins the render-pass test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4619 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:599:- Added depth-2 local-client end-to-end test coverage (frac-0064): `tests/test_client_local.py` now includes `TestLocalAdaClientEndToEnd`, which drives the existing `LocalAdaClient` public surface through typed `GenerationRequest` and legacy mapping paths. The new tests verify typed requests produce real mono WAV previews with stable local request ids, protocol summaries, zero-cost metadata, expected latency from an injected clock, valid WAV container metadata, nonzero frames, and passing `validate_generation_result` outcomes; verify mapping requests return queue/cache/storage-ready payloads with `prediction_id`, `api_request_id`, `request_id`, `audio_path`, `sample_rate`, duration, model, cost, per-second cost, and nonnegative latency; round-trip request summaries and combined diagnostics through `json.dumps`; and confirm repeated mapping generation reuses the same deterministic path and bytes. `tests/test_test_client_local_depth.py` pins `tests/test_client_local.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing local-client assertions and production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4414 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:703:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:705:- Added depth-2 generation client_protocol helpers (frac-0010): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` now exposes a frozen `GenerationOutcome` dataclass plus pure helpers `cost_per_second`, `result_summary`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` so any backend (Replicate, Modal, local Ada, fakes) can compute USD-per-second cost from a `GenerationResult`, render a stable operator-readable summary dict (rounded duration / cost / per-second cost), emit a single-line `model=… dur=…s cost=$… latency=…ms id=…` log entry with `<unknown>` substituted for an empty `api_request_id`, and validate a result against its `GenerationRequest` (model match, sample-rate floor, duration tolerance, non-negative cost, non-negative latency) into a typed pass/fail outcome with stable reason ordering. The existing `GenerationResult` field order, `GenerationClient` Protocol contract, and downstream `client_replicate` / `client_modal` / `client_local` paths are preserved; `tests/test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins outcome shape, zero-duration cost handling, summary rounding, log-line ID fallback, and accumulated validation reasons, while existing client protocol, Replicate retry, Modal, local-Ada, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:743:- Added a steady-state SDP cap summary (T-032@c): `promptclaw.sdp_cost` now exposes `DailyCapCheck`, `CostCapSummary`, `read_csv`, `check_daily_caps`, `summarize_daily_cap`, `render_cap_summary`, and `write_cap_summary`, plus optional CLI flags `--summary-out`, `--daily-cap-usd`, and `--min-days`. The committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cap-summary.md` links to `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md`, checks seven active UTC days from `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` against the documented `$5.00` daily cap, and reports **FAIL** with seven breaches. Regression coverage in `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` pins exact-at-cap pass behavior, breach overage formatting, minimum-day failure behavior, CLI failure status on breach, and the committed summary artifact.
CHANGELOG.md:745:- Added a steady-state SDP cost extractor and committed CSV (T-032@b): `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` exposes `TOKEN_PRICING`, `match_pricing`, `call_cost_usd`, `DailyCostRow`, `extract_steady_state_cost`, and `write_csv`, applying the substring-matched pricing table from `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` (claude-opus-4 $15/$75, claude-sonnet-4 $3/$15, claude-haiku $0.80/$4, gpt-4o $2.50/$10, o3 $10/$40, codex-mini $1.50/$6, fallback $3/$15) to per-task `lead_profile_id` rows in the `.sdp/state.db` `telemetry` table. The CLI `python -m promptclaw.sdp_cost --db .sdp/state.db --days 7 --out sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` rolls the 7 most recent active UTC days into the committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` (header `date,runs,input_tokens,output_tokens,cache_creation_tokens,cache_read_tokens,total_cost_usd,models`); `cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, and `thinking_tokens` are reported but not billed, matching the cost-model.md formula. Test coverage in `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` pins the pricing table values, substring-and-fallback matching, the cost-model.md worked example (`(in/1e6*in_p)+(out/1e6*out_p)`), per-day grouping with sorted unique tier lists, the locked CSV header schema with 4-decimal USD formatting and `|`-joined models, and the CLI's stdout path echo.
CHANGELOG.md:755:- Added a live Replicate smoke test for the generation backend (T-005): `tests/test_generation_live_replicate.py` exercises `ReplicateClient.generate(req)` against the real Replicate API with a fixed prompt and seed, and asserts a >100 KB WAV payload, `cost_usd` inside `[$0.01, $0.50]`, and `latency_ms < 60000`. The test is gated behind both the new `--run-live-replicate` pytest flag (registered in `tests/conftest.py` alongside the existing `--run-live-modal` seam) and a non-empty `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, so the default `pytest tests/` run skips it. Documented as ~$0.10 per opted-in run.
CHANGELOG.md:898:- Added a Telegram `/local` built-in backed by a shared daemon status snapshot so operators can request per-socket Ollama health, loaded models, and latency on demand.
CHANGELOG.md:899:- Wired `ollama_health()` into the `/status` Telegram command and half-hour heartbeat so operators can see per-socket Ollama health, loaded models, and latency without SSH.
CHANGELOG.md:900:- Added daemon-local `ollama_health()` dual-socket reporting for ports `11434` and `11435`, including per-instance loaded models and measured probe latency.

